Forum

ReplyGuitar playing thread

at 21:40 12 Aug 2024

Any ageing muso help me with this ?

My wife was watching TV and I was doing the crossword and having a beer as per usual.

Mention was made on TV of a majorette. Immediately a song came into what I call my mind. I think it was 70s, probably English and a line in the chorus was “she's a majorette” with the singer's voice lifting sharply to utter “majorette”

I can't get it out of my head.

Nothing on Google. Forum

ReplyThis Sky deal?

at 20:22 12 Aug 2024

I wrote to the EFL once and was just brushed off. I wrote to Sky expressing my concern about how many of our matches they'd “picked” and I don't think they read my letter as the reply said. “ don't worry there'll be plenty of opportunities to watch your team on Sky. Forum

ReplyThis Sky deal?

Reply12.30pm Saturday kick off.

at 09:27 11 Aug 2024

Sky of course have little but contempt for the fans.

The clubs have sold their loyal fans down the river.

The TV money was of course too high to reject but as we all know, extra money coming in goes straight to the pockets of players and agents.

I hated yesterday. Still, only two months 'til the first Saturday game… Forum
